			<head type="mainTitle">Chapter 1</head>
			<head type="subTitle">Peter Breaks Through</head>
			<p xml:lang="en" n="1">All children, except one, grow up. They 
				soon know that they will grow up, 
				and the way <name type="person" resp="#EB">Wendy</name> knew was this. 
				One day when <rs type="person">she</rs> was 
				<num type="cardinal" value="2">two</num> years old <rs type="person">she</rs> was playing in a <name type="place">garden</name>, and <rs type="person">she</rs> plucked another 
				flower and ran with it to <rs type="person">her</rs> mother. I suppose 
				<rs type="person">she</rs> must have looked rather delightful, for <name type="person" resp="#EB"><choice resp="#EB"><abbr>Mrs</abbr><expan>Missus</expan></choice> 
				Darling</name> put <rs type="person">her</rs> hand to <rs type="person">her</rs> heart and cried, 
				<q type="thought">Oh, why can't you remain like this for ever!</q> 
				This was all that passed between <rs type="person">them</rs> on the 
				subject, but henceforth <name type="person" resp="#EB">Wendy</name> knew that <rs type="person">she</rs> must grow up. You always know after you are 
				<num type="cardinal" value="2">two</num>. <num type="cardinal" value="2">Two</num> is the beginning of the end.</p>
